-- Toronto-Dominion Names Pedersen to Replace Hatanaka in Asset Management
-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 2010-11-01T15:24:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/toronto-dominion-names-pedersen-to-replace-hatanaka-in-asset-management.html
Toronto-Dominion Bank , Canada’s
second-largest lender, named  Michael Pedersen  group head of
wealth management, replacing  William Hatanaka .  Hatanaka, a former Ottawa Rough Riders football player who
 joined  the Toronto-based bank in 2003, will be staying until the
end of 2011 to advise Pedersen. The change was confirmed by
Toronto-Dominion spokesman Wojtek Dabrowski.  Pedersen, who starts in the new role today, was  previously 
group head of corporate operations at Toronto-Dominion. He was
with Barclays Plc in London as head of global private banking
and two international businesses, and a past chairman of the
Canadian Bankers Association.  Profit at Toronto-Dominion’s wealth management unit, which
includes results from its stake in TD Ameritrade Holding Corp.,
was C$179 million ($176 million) in the fiscal third quarter,
representing about 15 percent of overall  profit . The bank is
scheduled to release fourth-quarter results Dec. 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
